Package controller

Class CustomerController

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.Controller
      • controller.WindowController
        • controller.CustomerController
  • public class CustomerController
extends WindowController
    Controller for managing the windows that add and modify customers. It constructs the forms, waits for user input, delegates to the Customer class for validating the user-provided fields, and delegates to CustomerDao to perform the database operation to add or update the customer.
    Author:
    Joseph T. Lapp

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize()
        Initializes the customer form, including populating the combo boxes and setting initial field values when modifying an customer.

        LAMBDA - This lambda replaces what would have been another method and passing a reference to that method instead of passing this lambda. The lambda prevents me from having to write that method. In addition to requiring less code, the lambda code is clearer, because the lambda presents the event behavior directly alongside the object to which it responds (countryComboBox).

      • populateDivisionField

        private void populateDivisionField​(java.lang.String forCountry)
        Populate the country "first level division" combo box for a given country.

        LAMBDA - These two lambdas together implement a loop that selects only the divisions of a particular country. It is possible to write this as a loop in the same number of lines (three), but only by excluding curly braces for both the 'for' loop and its nested 'if' condition -- not good programming practice. So there is slightly less code, but in addition, the lambda presentation is declarative, offering a non-procedural statement of what is done, which some people may find clearer.

        Parameters:
        forCountry - Country to which to restrict division options
